Jenna Etheridge, News24SA Police. (Duncan Alfreds, News24, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Three-year-old Courtney Peters is still nowhere to be found after she went missing in Elsies River earlier in the week, Western Cape police said on Saturday. Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana said the search was ongoing. The girl was last seen at 08:00 on Thursday at the corner of Milky Way and Grand View Avenue According to the Pink Ladies, an organisation for missing children, she was wearing a white and yellow t-shirt with blue shorts, and walking barefoot. She is described as having dark hair and eyes, flat ears, and a small nose. She is of medium weight and average height, and she was last seen with pigtails. Police have asked anyone who has seen the missing child, or who might have information to contact Warrant Officer Lawrence on 079 894 0107 or Elsie's River SAPS on 021 933 0308. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.